<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-09-01T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-09-01T11:00:00-05:00" n="687" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d687">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">352.1815/3: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Consul at Barcelona</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Franklin</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-09-01T12:00:00-04:00">September 1,
                                        1936—noon</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Department’s August 29, 2 p.m., your August 30, noon.<note n="9" xml:id="d687fn9">Neither printed.</note> The Department desires
                                you to maintain cordial contact with the Costa Rican Consul and
                                requests you to extend all proper and consistent assistance to him
                                or his successor in the protection or evacuation of Costa Rican
                                nationals should the need arise.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>